http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Regulating-rush-the-SCR-way/article13994587.ece

The South Central Railway (SCR) has announced doubling of the platform ticket for Secunderabad railway station from Rs. 10 to Rs. 20 for a week – January 12 to January 18. An official spokesman informed that in view of the ensuing Sankranti festival coinciding with the Sabarimalai traffic, the premier station is expected to see a surge in travellers and also non-travellers, leading to huge crowd on the platforms during the period. Therefore, to regulate the flow of people and avoid inconvenience to the travelling, rate of platform ticket fee has been hiked.Special trainsSCR has also released schedule for another set of special trains to tackle the festival surge of travellers.(1) Train No. 07075 Secunderabad-Kakinada Town (via Kazipet), will depart Secunderabad at 8.45 p.m. on January 14 and arrive Kakinada Town at 5.30 a.m. on the next day. (2) Train No. 07076 Kakinada Town – Secunderabad Special will depart Kakinada at 4.45 p.m. on January 17 and arrive Secunderabad at 5.50 a.m. on the next day.Kazipet, Warangal, Khammam, Vijayawada, Eluru, Tadepalligudem, Rajahmundry and Samalkot stations are the stops.(3) Train No. 07431 / 07432 Kakinada Town - Tirupati – Kakinada Town Special Train (via Vijayawada), will depart Kakinada Town at 4.45 p.m. on Jan. 15 and arrive Tirupati at 7.10 a.m. on the next day. In return direction, Train No. 07432 Tirupati – Kakinada Town Special train will depart Tirupati at 7 p.m. on Jan.16 and arrive Kakinada Town at 5 a.m. on the next day.